/* Count the number of pixels in image with each grayscale intensity.
   The vector `image` is a grayscale image with values 0-255.
   Store the results in `bins`.

   The implementation uses a thread‑local histogram to avoid cache
   contention, then combines the histograms once.  The function
   preserves the exact semantics of the original.
